               <faith type="EOTC"/>

               <floruit notBefore="1708" notAfter="1711">He was a Gondarine king who succeeded his nephew
                  <persName ref="PRS9152TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot I</persName> in<date>1708</date>.
                  He came to throne at the instigation of one
                  of the court notables, <persName ref="PRS10473Yostos">Yosṭos</persName>, who later succeeded him.
                  Shortly after his accession to power,
                  <persName ref="PRS9449Tewoflos">Tewoflos</persName>
                  issued a proclamation establishing the doctrine of Qǝbāt as an official teaching of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church.
                  This proclamation was challenged by the Tawāḥǝdo party.
                  He faced also the challenges of several pretenders. </floruit>
               <death when="1711">He died of illness.</death>

